9: Hi, Mia! What's all this stuff?
14:
These lil' beauties? These are some
of the treasures I've collected from
ruins around the world. Just finished
cleaning 'em up!
19:
Wow! I've never seen anything like
them. Hmm... What's this one for?
23: It separates egg yolks from whites!
33:
You just pop in an egg and give this
part a squeeze. Then the yolk and
white end up here and... Here!
36:
Oh, that makes sense... I think?
I'm not sure WHY you'd need one,
but it's pretty neat! How about this
thing over here?
46:
As in, a spectacular spatula?
Is it different from normal ones?
49:
You bet it is! Check this out;
it's flexible, so you can do THIS.
54:
Whoa! It scraped the side of the bowl
clean in one swipe! I guess that IS
pretty spectacular.
56:
Hmm...
Is it just me, or do a lot of these
treasures seem a little mundane?
61:
M-mun...dane? Um, well, I mean—
Oh! What about this one?
73:
Dunno, but it's got "IXER" written on
the side. When you push the button,
these funky little blades spin around
super fast! Cool, right?
76:
This bad boy could shred a monster
to ribbons! To be honest, it kinda
freaks me out, so I've never actually
used it, though.
80:
Oh, Mia... I hate to do this to you, but...
Hand it over for a second.
83:
See how it whirls?
I think this was used to mix batter...
91:
Argh, I can't believe it... The Ixer Blade,
it was just a kitchen utensil?
103:
This stuff is amazing, Mia! We could
whip up a cake in no time! Where did
you find all of these?
106:
Uh, lemme think... I'm pretty sure
I got 'em from a treasure chest in
the Kaleidoscope. You can have them
if you want.
111:
Oh my gosh, are you sure?
I'd love them, but they're your
special treasures, aren't they?
115:
Go for it! Treasures belong with
someone who can really
appreciate 'em, right?
121:
...On one condition!
I call dibs on a slice of cake!
124:
Haha, of course! I'll make the best
cake you've ever had!
128:
Aw, I'm just glad my little treasures
are gonna be put to good use.
131:
Moments like this are what keep me
goin'! Just you wait, I'll get my paws
on the best treasure ever someday!
